                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>, full color and with excellent and refined artistic skills. By artist 2</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> at the Crossing of the Red Sea, with The Egyptian King and army (all showing one eye) on the left (<locus target="#iiv(erso)">fol. iiv(erso)</locus>) and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7182Moses">Moses</persName> and the Children of Israel being guided by Mika'el on the right. By artist 2</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName>, standing with <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/> and drawn <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/>. With caption <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሊቀ ትጕሃን</foreign>, Archangel of the Watchers. By artist 1, the presumed original painter</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#6v" facs="011">Fol. 6v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> Enthroned. By artist 2</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#7r" facs="011">Fol. 7r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> flying above a sinner (showing one eye) burning in fire. By artist 2</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    Three Multi-generational genealogical lists, in Amharic. The first is for at least seven generations (first paragraph), the second one is for seven generations in the second paragraph (col 1‒2), the third is a list of eleven generations (third paragraph)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="005">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Despite the label on folio 1r, the Weiner collection number should be 461 and not 458
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="005">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Elaborate harags
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#14r #21r #22r" facs="018 025 026">Fols. 14r, 21r, 22r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    At various places one <foreign xml:lang="gez">መስቀለ፡ ቃል፡</foreign>, the likely original owner, is mentioned (e.g., <locus target="#14r #21r" facs="018 025">fols. 14r, 21r</locus>),
                    also called <foreign xml:lang="gez">መስቀለ፡ ቃል፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign> (<locus target="#22r" facs="026">fol. 22r</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#126v #127r" facs="131">Fols. 126v, 127r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    This book belongs to Masqala qal (<foreign xml:lang="gez">መስቀለ፡ ቃል፡</foreign>) and his father Yawordanos (<foreign xml:lang="gez">የዎርዳኖስ፡</foreign>) and his mother (<foreign xml:lang="gez">የርስና፡</foreign>) Yarsana, and his wife (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>) Walata Iyasus, and his son Maramawit (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ማራምአዊት፡</foreign>).
                    The name of a secondary owner appears at several junctures, both in this colophon text, and elsewhere, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡</foreign>.
                    The scribe is also mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a">
                    <locus target="#127v #128r #128v #129r #129v #130r #130v #132r" facs="132 133 134 135 136"> f. 132r, column 1</locus>
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    Multiple records of Land Transactions with witnesses, appointments to the church, records of inheritance of gult, etc.
                    Approximately three records per page. Some of the records seem to presuppose the general location from which the book comes:
                    Entoto Maryam or Entoto Raguel, since the word <foreign xml:lang="am">እንጦጦ፡</foreign> appears several times.
                    The following person figures prominently in several of the records, <foreign xml:lang="am">አቶ፡ ነሲቡ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
